          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a kind of manual or handbook to be used by a priest, outlining the rules and religious laws governing the construction and installation of fire to be used in various Hindu and Vedic rites, such as wrist binding, the veneration of deities, and other ceremonies. There is a minor text of five lines written by a second hand at the end of the manuscript called Yajñāntagodāna. The word "Gopaldit" is written in large letters in Roman script on the back of the manuscript. Manuscript is incomplete, missing the first folio.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Agnisthāpanavidhi</title>
              <title type="vernacular">अग्निस्थापनविधि</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Lohan, Viṣnudatta Dvijavara</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: ity agnisthāpanavidhiḥ samāptaṃ śubham lekhakapāṭhakayoḥ śrīśāke 1782 samvat 1918 vaiśākhakṛṣṇa 11 ravivāsare kāśyāṃ dvijavaraviṣṇudattalohan upādhyāyena likhitam idam pustakam // (f. 17v).</colophon>
